projectInfo.shortDescription:
- Author: HOT
- Requesting Organization: **Tanzania Development Trust**

Tanzania has a high incidence of  Child Marriage and Gender Based Violence. NGOs on the ground need better mapping to facilitate their outreach work.

The Missing Maps project aims to map the most vulnerable places in the world (affected by humanitarian crises: disease epidemics, conflict, natural disasters, poverty, environmental crises). Building on HOT's disaster preparedness projects, the Missing Maps tasks facilitate pre-emptive mapping of priority countries to better facilitate disaster response, medical activities and resource allocation when crises occur.

projectInfo.instructions:
Project Specific Mapping Notes
=========================
* **Imagery Note** Please use **Maxar Premium** imagery.  
* **PLEASE UPDATE MAPPING TO MAXAR PREMIUM ALIGNMENT**
* Please trace buildings from the satellite images. 
*  All highways should join up, even if the exact location is not clear.
* Local mappers: [Local knowledge tags and images](https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B_2QVFnCIYvpVHdJMmZXREZqRHc/view) (Interesting for remote mappers too!)

* General remote mapping tutorials: [Beginner Learn-To-Map Videos](http://www.missingmaps.org/learn/#beginner)  and [LearnOSM](http://learnosm.org/en/)
* Use the **"Split"** link after you click "Start Mapping" to make tiles smaller if needed.

If you have not yet achieved your **Buildings 101 Badge** by getting 100% in the online quiz, please do so here https://canvas.instructure.com/enroll/JAHNEB 
Buildings 101 helps mappers to map buildings correctly. It features video clips, links to resources, and a short training quiz.

We also have a **Crowd2Map Slack channel** where we offer feedback and support, news and chat about the project. If you would like to join, please message #managers in this project's comments to receive the current link to join.

**Most Commonly used tags:**

- building=yes


Buildings
=======
* Please accurately outline all the buildings you can find. The outline should be for the full size of the building even if it is partly covered by trees in the imagery.
* For square or rectangular buildings, after drawing the outline, **use the 'q' key in the web editor to "square" the corners**.
* In the iD web editor, the first time you map a building you will use the "Building" category and then at the top of the list select "Building" again.
* Many of the buildings are round, you can watch a [1 minute video demonstrating a fast way to map round buildings in iD Web Editor](https://youtu.be/CX4T6uOi7HE)
OSM map features page for more info.

Some of the buildings are fine, but there are a few issues: when adding buildings, check that you don't mistake the shadow for the building itself. Zooming out a bit (before zooming in to do the actual drawing) can help you decide on the shape and size. Please square buildings by using the 'q' key, don't include the surrounding area and make sure to map buildings individually (rather than several as one). You can learn more about how to map buildings in Buildings 101 - a short training module (should take less than 20 minutes to complete) that helps mappers to map buildings correctly. It features short video clips, links to resources, and a training quiz.  On completion you earn a digital badge: https://canvas.instructure.com/enroll/JAHNEB You could also join the Slack team for Crowd2Map - check the project page for more info.Thanks again, and please keep mapping!
